Algernon Chester-Master (27 September 1851 – 1 September 1897) was an English cricketer.
Chester-Master represented Gloucestershire in two first-class matches in 1870, against Surrey and the Marylebone Cricket Club.Chester-Master died at Northampton, Northamptonshire on 1 September 1897.
